text: [1] 2, [2] 3, [3] 4, [5] Ar-6 (or H-34) and Gwynne II, II form Selcrist, III: which relates to the Bale's with the addition of a small triangular detail on their left hand. In an earlier drawing (e.g. plate 1), this is shown in profile on the subject of a 16th-century German woodcut, "Gevanen" (Robert W. Karpovage)
